---
export interface Props {
  showFloorSystem?: boolean;
  showPressureCalc?: boolean;
}

const { showFloorSystem = true, showPressureCalc = false } = Astro.props;
---

<div class="nbc-waterproofing bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center">
    <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">💧</span>
    NBC 9.13.3 Waterproofing System Requirements
  </h3>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
      <h4 class="font-bold mb-3 text-cyan-700">Required Conditions</h4>
      <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
          <span>Hydrostatic pressure present</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
          <span>Water table above floor level</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
          <span>Blocked/inadequate drainage</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
          <span>Wet site conditions</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4">
      <h4 class="font-bold mb-3 text-cyan-700">Material Standards</h4>
      <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
          <span>Two-membrane minimum</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
          <span>Emulsified/cut-back asphalt</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
          <span>Glass fiber reinforcement</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
          <span>CAN/CGSB compliance</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  {showFloorSystem && (
    <div class="bg-amber-50 border-2 border-amber-400 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-bold mb-4 text-lg flex items-center">
        <span class="text-2xl mr-3">⚠️</span>
        NBC 9.13.3.5 Floor Waterproofing System
      </h4>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">System Components</h5>
          <ol class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li><strong>1.</strong> Bottom concrete slab (min 75mm)</li>
            <li><strong>2.</strong> Waterproof membrane system</li>
            <li><strong>3.</strong> Top wearing slab (min 75mm)</li>
            <li><strong>4.</strong> Continuous wall-floor seal</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Critical Details</h5>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>• Membrane between two slabs</li>
            <li>• Lap with wall membrane</li>
            <li>• Complete envelope seal</li>
            <li>• Protect during construction</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-amber-50 rounded">
        <p class="text-sm">
          <strong>Important:</strong> Floor membrane must be continuous with wall waterproofing to create 
          complete hydrostatic barrier. Any discontinuity will result in water infiltration.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  )}

  {showPressureCalc && (
    <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-300 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-bold mb-4 text-lg text-red-700">Hydrostatic Pressure Calculations</h4>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Pressure Formula</h5>
          <div class="bg-white rounded p-3 font-mono text-sm">
            P = ρ × g × h
          </div>
          <ul class="text-sm mt-3 space-y-1">
            <li><strong>P</strong> = Pressure (kPa)</li>
            <li><strong>ρ</strong> = Water density (1000 kg/m³)</li>
            <li><strong>g</strong> = Gravity (9.81 m/s²)</li>
            <li><strong>h</strong> = Water depth (m)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Typical Pressures</h5>
          <table class="w-full text-sm bg-white rounded">
            <thead class="bg-red-100">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left">Water Depth</th>
                <th class="px-3 py-2">Pressure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b">
                <td class="px-3 py-2">0.5m (20")</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 text-center font-bold">4.9 kPa</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b">
                <td class="px-3 py-2">1.0m (39")</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 text-center font-bold">9.8 kPa</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b">
                <td class="px-3 py-2">2.0m (79")</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 text-center font-bold">19.6 kPa</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-3 py-2">3.0m (118")</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 text-center font-bold">29.4 kPa</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-red-100 rounded">
        <p class="text-sm">
          <strong>Buoyancy Warning:</strong> If water table rises >200mm (8") above floor, 
          upward pressure exceeds slab weight. Special slab design required per NBC Part 4.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  )}

  <div class="bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-4">
    <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">Surface Preparation (NBC 9.13.3.3)</h4>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
      <div>
        <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Concrete Walls</h5>
        <ul class="space-y-1">
          <li>• Remove projections</li>
          <li>• Fill tie holes</li>
          <li>• Smooth surface</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div>
        <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">Masonry Walls</h5>
        <ul class="space-y-1">
          <li>• 6mm parging</li>
          <li>• Coved at footing</li>
          <li>• Smooth finish</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div>
        <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2">All Surfaces</h5>
        <ul class="space-y-1">
          <li>• Clean and dry</li>
          <li>• No ice or frost</li>
          <li>• No contaminants</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-4 text-xs text-slate-500 border-t pt-3">
    <p><strong>Reference:</strong> NBC 2015 Part 9, Section 9.13.3 - Waterproofing</p>
    <p>Professional waterproofing required where hydrostatic pressure exists.</p>
  </div>
</div>